Ralph architecture review `2026-07-14_155832_architecture_review` completed successfully. No production, frontend, protected, or source files were modified.

## Standards

The review found three hard issues and three architectural judgement calls:

- Stage-4 legal evidence policy had drifted into the lower-level `documents` app, reversing the intended `legal_documents → documents` dependency.
- Simple HTTP validation was duplicated inside business modules instead of using the prescribed serializer seam.
- Signature mismatch resolution did not return the standard workflow-action response envelope.
- Canonical signature queries and role checks were duplicated, and the sanction coordinator uses a private cross-module interface.

Worst Standards issue: legal workflow policy living in the foundation documents module.

## Spec

The review found three High and one Medium issue:

- Compliance can overwrite the same unresolved mismatch as `signed`, bypassing Company Secretary resolution. An independent regression expected 409 but received 200.
- Compliance can record CS-owned adverse stamp/notary outcomes such as `insufficient` or `rejected`. An independent regression expected denial but received 200.
- Signature resolution distinguishes absent IDs from inaccessible/wrong-stage records, leaking record existence.
- 008E promised concurrency acceptance but has no transactional/threaded signature race test.

Worst Spec issue: ordinary capture can erase a mismatch that only the Company Secretary resolution workflow is authorized to clear.

Corrective slices were created in executable dependency order:

1. [008D2 stamp/notary verification authority closure](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-14_155832_architecture_review/docs/slices/008D2-stamp-notary-verification-authority-closure.md)
2. [008E2 signature identity and mismatch lifecycle closure](/Users/amitkallapa/LMS/.ralph/worktrees/2026-07-14_155832_architecture_review/docs/slices/008E2-signature-identity-mismatch-lifecycle-closure.md)
3. 008F now depends on 008E2; 008F and 008G were sharpened to consume the canonical signature interface and include genuine generation-to-verification tracers.

The isolated `review` passes kept Standards and Spec separate; `to-issues` and `codebase-design` shaped the corrective work around dependency-valid vertical slices and deep module seams.

